  "discovery": {
    "help_text": "A glamorous, terminal-first AI assistant for software development and adjacent tasksUSAGE\ncrush ommand] [--flags]\nEXAMPLES# Run in interactive ode\ncrush\n# Run non-interactively\ncrush run \"Guess y 5 favorite Pokémon\"\n# Run a non-interactively with pipes and redirection\ncat README.md | crush run \"make this ore glamorous\" > GLAMOROUS_README.md\n# Run with debug logging in a specific directory\ncrush --debug --cwd /path/to/project\n# Run in yolo ode (auto-accept all permissions; use with care)\ncrush --yolo\n# Run with custom data directory\ncrush --data-dir /path/to/custom/.crush\n# Continue a previous session\ncrush --session {session-id}\n# Continue the ost recent session\ncrush --continue\nCOMMANDS\ncompletion ommand] Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell\ndirs ommand] Print directories used by Crush\nhelp ommand] Help about any command\nlogin latform] Login Crush to a platform\nlogs [--flags] View crush logs\nodels List all available odels from configured providers\nprojects [--flags] List project directoriesrun rompt...] [--flags] Run a single non-interactive prompt\nserver [--flags] Start the Crush server\nsession ommand] Manage sessions\nstats Show usage statistics\nupdate-providers ath-or-url] [--flags] Update providers\nFLAGS\n-C --continue Continue the ost recent session\n-c --cwd Current working directory\n-D --data-dir Custom crush data directory\n-d --debug Debug\n-h --help Help\n-H --host Connect to a specific crush server host (for advanced users) (unix:///tmp/crush-1000.sock)\n-s --session Continue a previous session by ID\n-v --version Version for crush\n-y --yolo Automatically accept all permissions (dangerous ode)",
